            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Trenten</sic> N. J</placeName>
                <date>9 Augt./66</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have received your<lb/> favor of <date>6th</date> inst. and was
                pained<lb/> to learn that my son <persName>Abraham</persName> had<lb/> imposed upon
                yr. kindness. He is<lb/> unfortunately not right in his mind<lb/> and still not
                sufficiently so to war=<lb/>-rant his confinement in an asylum.<lb/> He has
                occasioned his mother &amp;<lb/> myself great unhappiness. Altho'<lb/> I appreciate
                your motive in assisting<lb/> him I regret you did so, because<lb/> there was no
                necessity for his absence<lb/> from home; -I send you enclosed<lb/> $5. in paymt. of
                what you were kind<lb/> enough to advance him. He is still<lb/> absent, &amp; should
                he apply to you<lb/> again I hope you will refuse him.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>and if you happen to see him lecture<lb/> him as severely as you can.â€”.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With best <add>respects</add> from <persName>Mrs
                    Haart<add>?</add></persName> &amp; my family I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours very resfuly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Dd. Haart</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
